Introduction

Taeho is a South Korean singer and songwriter currently signed under HAM. He is a member of the boy group IMFACT and made his solo debut on May 27, 2021, with the digital single Ggoma.

Taeho debuted with IMFACT on January 27, 2016, with the single album Lollipop. After parting ways with Star Empire Entertainment in January 2022, he signed with HAM in 2024 and released the digital single For Your Brilliant Day on May 28. Later that year, he made his Japanese debut with the single I Like You on September 13, followed by a Korean version on October 2. Taeho also announced a duet concert with Hong Eunki, further showcasing his diverse talents as an artist.
